[2026-01-23 15:41:27] [INFO] EvaluationRunner: response: Here's a simple example of building a RAG service in Spring AI, based on the provided context:

```java
@RestController
class MyController {

    private final ChatClient chatClient;

    public MyController(ChatClient.Builder chatClientBuilder) {
        this.chatClient = chatClientBuilder.build();
    }

    @GetMapping("/ai")
    String generation(String userInput) {
        return this.chatClient.prompt()
            .user(userInput)
            .call()
            .content();
    }
}
```

**Explanation:**

*   **`@RestController`**:  This annotation marks the class as a REST controller, handling incoming web requests.
*   **`ChatClient chatClient;`**: This declares a field to hold an instance of the `ChatClient`, which is used to interact with the AI model.
*   **`MyController(ChatClient.Builder chatClientBuilder)`**: This is the constructor. Spring AI's autoconfiguration provides a `ChatClient.Builder` bean, which is injected here.  The builder is then used to create a `ChatClient` instance.
*   **`@GetMapping("/ai")`**: This annotation maps the `/ai` endpoint to the `generation` method, handling GET requests.
*   **`String generation(String userInput)`**: This method takes the user's input as a string.
*   **`this.chatClient.prompt().user(userInput).call().content();`**: This is the core of the interaction:
    *   `this.chatClient.prompt()`: Creates a prompt object.
    *   `.user(userInput)`: Sets the user's input as the message for the AI.
    *   `.call()`: Sends the prompt to the AI model and receives a response.
    *   `.content()`: Extracts the AI model's response as a String.

This example demonstrates the simplest use case, where Spring AI provides a `ChatClient.Builder` bean through autoconfiguration.  It retrieves a String response from the AI model based on the user's input.

For a more comprehensive RAG example with MongoDB, refer to the [detailed tutorial](https://www.mongodb.com/developer/languages/java/retrieval-augmented-generation-spring-ai/).

